Marbor River at the type locality is a small, premontane river, 15-22 m wide, with depths up to 1.5-1.7 m (
Fig. 10A
). The river bed is braided and formed of coarse and fine gravel, with sparse cobbles. At the type locality the river formed two approximately equal branches with fast, turbulent flow (0.4-0.9 m/s), and a wide alluvium. The larvae inhabited the gravel substratum in the fast flow of the streamline, but were also found in the littoral zone.

